Date: 27 Aug 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: OIE Disease Information, 26 Aug 2005, Vol. 18 - No. 34 [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/eng/info/hebdo/a_current.htm#Sec9>

Foot and mouth disease in Mongolia
-----------------------------------------
Follow-up report No. 1 (identification of virus type Asia 1).

See also: 19 Aug 2005, 22 Oct 2004.
Information received on 26 Aug 2005 from Dr. Doloonjin Orgil, Director,
Department of Veterinary Services, Ministry of Food and Agriculture,
Ulaanbaatar:
End of previous report period: 18 Aug 2005 (see Disease Information, 18
[33], 271, dated 19 Aug 2005).
End of this report period: 26 Aug 2005.
No new outbreaks have been reported.
Total number of animals in the outbreak (updated data):
species / susceptible / cases / deaths / destroyed / slaughtered
bov / 118 / 118 / ... / 118 / 0
o/c / 47 / 47 / ... / 47 / 0
Diagnosis:
A. Laboratory where diagnosis was confirmed: samples were sent to the
laboratory of the Federal Centre for Animal Health in Vladimir, Russia (OIE
Reference Laboratory for foot and mouth disease).
B. Causal agent: the test results were received on 22 Aug 2005: virus type
Asia 1 was identified.
Control measures:
- quarantine;
- stamping out;
- movement control;
- zoning;
- disinfection.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[The OIE Reference Laboratory for foot and mouth disease has updated the
diagnosis of this virus to Asia 1 instead of the previously reported Type A
FMD virus. - Mod.PC]
